oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Copy of a photograph of James W. Webb and his family
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: James W. Webb wore his Grand Army of the Republic badge in this family photograph with his wife Susan Melvinia Turner Webb, and two daughters, Alice Foster Webb (White), Nellie Webb (Manning). Webb served in the Civil War as a private, Co. G,; 4th Tenn. Mtd. Inf., USA. He enlisted Jan. 23, 1865, contracted measles and was discharged Aug. 25, 1865.
